      { en: 'What are coronaviruses? Coronaviruses were discovered in the 1960s. They are a group of viruses that cause diseases in mammals and birds. In humans, coronaviruses cause respiratory tract infections. The new coronavirus. At the end of 2019, a new type of coronavirus started spreading in China. This type of coronavirus is often called 2019-nCoV, novel coronavirus, or COVID-19. It is believed that the virus was transmitted from animals to humans. Some of the first cases were diagnosed in people who had visited a market selling live seafood and animals.', zh: '什么是冠状病毒？冠状病毒于20世纪60年代被发现。它们是一组能在哺乳动物和鸟类中引发疾病的病毒。对人类而言，冠状病毒会引起呼吸道感染。关于新冠病毒：2019年底，一种新型冠状病毒开始在中国传播。这种病毒通常被称为2019-nCoV、新型冠状病毒或COVID-19。据认为，该病毒由动物传播给人类。部分首批确诊病例出现在曾去过售卖活海鲜和动物的市场的患者中。' },
      { en: 'Unfortunately, when viruses are transmitted from animals to people, it can take scientists a lot of time before they can develop a vaccine or medicines to cure it. How does the virus spread? The virus appears to spread mainly from person to person. The transmission occurs when someone comes into contact with an infected person. For example, a cough, a sneeze or a handshake could cause transmission.', zh: '不幸的是，当病毒从动物传播给人类时，科学家可能需要很长时间才能研发出疫苗或药物来治愈它。病毒如何传播？该病毒似乎主要在人与人之间传播。当某人与感染者接触时就会发生传播。例如，咳嗽、打喷嚏或握手都可能导致传播。' },
      { en: 'The spread may also be caused by coming into contact with something an infected person has touched and then touching your mouth, nose or eyes.', zh: '传播也可能通过接触感染者触摸过的物体，然后再触摸自己的口、鼻或眼睛而发生。' }
